01:03:17.260 --> 01:03:21.180
carbon dioxide, and makes
all the biomass we have--

01:03:21.180 --> 01:03:27.850
incredibly important in terms
of influencing the atmosphere.

01:03:27.850 --> 01:03:30.030
So two very quick
thoughts-- so one

01:03:30.030 --> 01:03:32.790
is, we should not
assume that our world is

01:03:32.790 --> 01:03:34.240
an aerobic world alone.

01:03:34.240 --> 01:03:36.670
There are plenty of anaerobic
environments in our world.

01:03:36.670 --> 01:03:40.440
And as Dave said, we're
very interested in the role

01:03:40.440 --> 01:03:42.292
that microbes play
in methane cycling.

01:03:42.292 --> 01:03:44.250
But there are also big
questions about the role

01:03:44.250 --> 01:03:47.420
they play in carbon
cycling, and just what's

01:03:47.420 --> 01:03:50.100
the fate of carbon that
